{
  "root": {
    "children": [
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "When humans wake up and find themselves lost in dungeons where they must fight their way through hordes of mutated enemies, a few questions spring to mind. In ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Despot's Game: Dystopian Army Builder",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ", guide your humans victory by playing \"the game\", equipping them with weapons (or whatever can make for a weapon) and guide them through the labyrinth. There's a lot to be discovered here in ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Despot's Game",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ", but it begs to question whether your minions will survive long enough to see it all.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "embed",
        "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=acYj0tt1j78",
        "html": "<iframe width=\"200\" height=\"113\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/acYj0tt1j78?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen title=\"Despot’s Game - Full Release Announcement Trailer\"></iframe>",
        "metadata": {
          "title": "Despot’s Game - Full Release Announcement Trailer",
          "author_name": "tinyBuildGAMES",
          "author_url": "https://www.youtube.com/c/tinyBuildGAMES",
          "height": 113,
          "width": 200,
          "version": "1.0",
          "provider_name": "YouTube",
          "provider_url": "https://www.youtube.com/",
          "thumbnail_height": 360,
          "thumbnail_width": 480,
          "thumbnail_url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/acYj0tt1j78/hqdefault.jpg"
        },
        "embedType": "video"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Good",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "koenig-heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1,
        "renderVersion": "4.0"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "RPG roguelites are a fascinating genre and ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Despot's Game",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " executes this to near-perfection. With the theme of obtaining disposable humans to do battle at your bidding, progressing through dungeons feels very rewarding (and don't worry, the pangs of guilt from repeatedly sending humans to their doom don't last long). However, you can't forget about your humans' wellbeing entirely as the more you have at your disposal, the more food you need to have for them. Each human will consume one point of food when proceeding from one room to the next (even if you've already been to the room before) and if you run out, they'll fight with less enthusiasm and will probably die. Food costs tokens, so you can't just buy the best fighters and weapons willy-nilly, and it's this balance that provides a tonne of strategy to the game. However, you'll need to find that balance as spending too much on food results in less tokens for new units and upgrades, which can result in an embarrassing death with a mountain of food and no mouths to feed it to.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Despot's Game",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " is also so snappy, meaning that proceeding from one room to the next or starting a new run is almost instant. You're always in the thick of things, whether it's combat or strategising, and there's rarely a dull moment. All roguelites can learn a thing or two from ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Despot's Game",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ", especially if you're a fan of the genre, because there's nothing worse than picking up a new roguelite and realising that the wait times between doing anything is unbearably slow.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Mutations allow you to add special abilities and stat boosts to your feeble little humans, providing you with a deeper level of customisation and strategy. You'll collect mutations throughout your journeys but you can also unlock more to find from the mutations menu; or rather, as the game puts it, \"invest in a steady future!\". This mechanic goes further than one would initially expect as after a few rounds, you'll begin to realise that with each unit's class, having a wide variety of units provides you with the depth and strategy needed to take down any enemy that comes your way. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The game's humour is wonderful, instantly poking fun of the video game medium by laughing at the \"Chosen One\" trope. Even your humans have names that can make you chuckle, which lead me to checking each one I came across. Sergei Hentai was an interesting one, and Scott Guts took me a few seconds to understand, but I felt a mix of laughter and personal shame when I finally did.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 9,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "SPOILER ALERT",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ": At the end of a runthrough, when you defeat Despot, you'll enter King of the Hill where your human troops duke it out against other real players' army that they had won with. This is a fantastic show of strength an encourages you to continue playing again and again so as to rank higher and higher online. However, you'll only be included on the leaderboard so long as you beat a run on at least Normal difficulty, so be sure to keep that in mind before starting a run.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
