      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Bad",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "koenig-heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1,
        "renderVersion": "4.0"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Despot's Game",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " was built for PC first and foremost, and it shows. While Konfa Games certainly made an effort to account for this as much as possible with the ability to turn the cursor controls off, working off of buttons and shoulder bumpers don't lend themselves well to the game's initial vision. Funnily enough, I opted to use the cursor mode with the controller, which is something that I don't often do with games that allow for the choice between cursor and button controls. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Despot's Game ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "features plenty of menu options and intricate characters to select, so the preciseness of the cursor lended itself better to the gameplay, despite it feeling clunky.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "As the game continued and I started to get the strategic hang of things, I found myself wanting to interact with the battles more so than just simply being a bystander. This was primarily the case in boss fights; units will simply attack the closest enemy to them, so I often ran into situations where every unit focused on the boss whilst all their lackies are wailing on my units with no one to stop them. This also seemed to be a similar issue with healers as they'll just heal whomever they choose to at that time; if I was able to direct their abilities towards key, high level units, they may have survived and I wouldn't have died in some crucial battles.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "While the music is quite banging at first, with it being an upbeat dance track with a half notes on the snare, quarter notes on the kick and sixteenth notes on the hi-hat for the most part, hearing that over-and-over again gets old real quick.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 1,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "TL;DR",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "UI/UX doesn't translate well to console",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
