      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "A good roguelite feels natural in its progression, providing the player with progression even when it may not feel like it at times. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Despot's Game",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " pulls this off wonderfully and doesn't try to overcomplicate itself, which it could have easily done if handled incorrectly. The humour is subjective but I found it to be a hoot, making me smile in-between combat sequences. And while you may feel like an awkward bystander at times, especially if you enjoy your more action-oriented roguelites, ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Despot's Game",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " does so much right that you can hardly fault it.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
